images.alt:
This is a panel on “Book History with Internet Data”, with 8 panelists from different IMLS/iSchools, funded by SHARP.

Over the past two decades, a variety of internet-based datasets have emerged related to books, reading habits, and reader communities—ranging from crowd-sourced genre tags and online reviews to platforms like BookTok. These datasets are increasingly valuable for research in reading and readership, often complementing traditional book history approaches. However, they also raise new questions and challenges. To explore these opportunities and foster interdisciplinary collaboration, this panel will bring together eight panelists from diverse fields to discuss questions, such as:

How can we critically understand the relationship between Internet-based “book” data and traditional research materials?
What are the methodological challenges and potential pitfalls of using digital data in book history research?
How can interdisciplinary approaches enrich the analysis of Internet book and reader datasets?

Trust your gut.
Humans are experts at noticing patterns, both where they break, and where they are abnormally perfect.

Exact Price Impact Breakdown Pre-deal (April 2025): WLFI was non-tradeable, valued at private round price of $0.05 (Trump family held 22.5B tokens worth ~$1.125B on paper). Immediate post-announcement surge (May 1–15, 2025): Token unlocked for accredited investors only → price jumped to $0.15–0.18 (+260–300%) purely on the news that a sovereign wealth fund chose USD1 for a $2B institutional deal. Summer buildup (June–August): Additional UAE-linked buys ($100M from Aqua1 Foundation on Sept 1) + pre-market futures on Binance/OKX hit $0.55 → WLFI became the most hyped launch of 2025. Launch day (Sept 1): Opened at $0.46, ATH $0.33 the next day → 660% from private sale price. CZ pardon spike (Oct 23): +14–15% in 24h directly attributed to the same UAE/Binance/WLFI nexus.  Why the deal mattered so much Legitimacy bomb: First time a sovereign wealth fund used a Trump-family stablecoin for a $2B institutional transaction → turned WLFI from "meme governance token" into "geopolitical DeFi infrastructure." Permanent revenue stream: Binance still holds most of the $2B USD1 → WLFI earns $60–85M annual interest (75% to Trump family). Network effect: Made USD1 the #6 stablecoin overnight → Binance spot listing on Oct 29 caused 1,550% market-cap surge in one week.  Current status (Nov 6, 2025) Price: $0.122–0.137 (down 60% from ATH but still +174% from private sale). Market cap: $3.0–3.3B (circulating). Trump family paper gains from their 22.5B tokens: ~$2.8B (at current price) — almost entirely thanks to the UAE deal turning WLFI into a "national strategic asset."  Bottom line: Without the $2B UAE/Binance/USD1 transaction, WLFI would still be a $0.05–0.08 niche governance token worth maybe $1–2B FDV. The deal was the match that lit the rocket — everything else (launch hype, pardon, listings) was just additional fuel. Degree of influence: 10/10 foundational.
